{"_id":"CIpPydJ3S9cClR0B","name":"Sage","type":"background","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-brown.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\">\n<p>You spent years learning the lore of the multiverse. You scoured manuscripts, studied scrolls, and listened to the greatest experts on the subjects that interest you. Your efforts have made you a master in your fields of study.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight)\" />\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\">\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Skill Proficiencies:</span></strong> @skill[Arcana], @skill[History]</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Languages:</span> </strong>Two of your choice</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Equipment:</span> </strong>A @item[Ink (1-ounce bottle)|phb|bottle of black ink], a quill, a small knife, a letter from a dead colleague posing a question you have not yet been able to answer, a set of @item[common clothes|phb], and a belt @item[pouch|phb] containing 10 gp</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<p><strong>Feature: </strong>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.NY0cE3MCTjzw3X3M]{Researcher}</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"2\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Specialty</span></h3>\n<p>To determine the nature of your scholarly training, roll a d8 or choose from the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.7nIJ47TPOKsuW6Bl]{Sage: Field of Study}</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"3\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Suggested Characteristics</span></h3>\n<p>Sages are defined by their extensive studies, and their characteristics reflect this life of study. Devoted to scholarly pursuits, a sage values knowledge highly—sometimes in its own right, sometimes as a means toward other ideals.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.JFPvplBI70B59lTf]{Sage: Personality Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.SGSIGMxVVQpSgHBk]{Sage: Ideal}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.mYLsnHQ99KADwa81]{Sage: Bond}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.qcMtCOieagNTeoM2]{Sage: Flaw}</p>\n</div>\n</div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Player's Handbook","advancement":[{"_id":"n4re4c8dtjm5ey6p","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.NY0cE3MCTjzw3X3M"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EbUDbuCjvuW36J0B":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hbRO096Dv1chMJDL"}}}
{"_id":"Dpk03mJO1jiQ6XVl","name":"Acolyte","type":"background","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/equipment/neck/necklace-runed-white-red.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have spent your life in the service of a temple to a specific god or pantheon of gods. You act as an intermediary between the realm of the holy and the mortal world, performing sacred rites and offering sacrifices in order to conduct worshipers into the presence of the divine. You are not necessarily a cleric—performing sacred rites is not the same thing as channeling divine power.</p>\n<p>Choose a god, a pantheon of gods, or some other quasi-divine being from among those listed in @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.2JNtWRo7wMq08bXn]{Fantasy-Historical Pantheons}, and work with your DM to detail the nature of your religious service. Were you a lesser functionary in a temple, raised from childhood to assist the priests in the sacred rites? Or were you a high priest who suddenly experienced a call to serve your god in a different way? Perhaps you were the leader of a small cult outside of any established temple structure, or even an occult group that served a fiendish master that you now deny.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:</strong> Insight, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> Two of your choice</p>\n<p><strong>Equipment: </strong>A holy symbol (a gift to you when you entered the priesthood), a prayer book or prayer wheel, 5 sticks of incense, @Compendium[dnd5e.items.irtqrzaUCeshmTZp]{vestments}, a set of @Compendium[dnd5e.items.8RXjiddJ6VGyE7vB]{common clothes}, and a pouch containing 15 gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Feature:</strong> @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.igvUOA7Lz2UKuEYe]{Shelter of the Faithful}</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Suggested Characteristics</h3>\n<p>Acolytes are shaped by their experience in temples or other religious communities. Their study of the history and tenets of their faith and their relationships to temples, shrines, or hierarchies affect their mannerisms and ideals. Their flaws might be some hidden hypocrisy or heretical idea, or an ideal or bond taken to an extreme.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.RRgD4lKLTiYLNGtU]{Acolyte: Personality Traits}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.shZpV9shZ74TjLkX]{Acolyte: Ideals}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.ZTjvolZTglDOHa8w]{Acolyte: Bonds}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.WItxw8NT5jL4sVyb]{Acolyte: Flaws}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules","advancement":[{"_id":"6grrnum72rnphzi5","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5e.backgrounds.64N1NWh9kC1dI7zN"]},"value":{},"level":0,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EbUDbuCjvuW36J0B":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dnd5e.backgrounds.IgJkSnLiLJOWH7eK"}}}
{"_id":"V3DSHhgBHvbqjSo2","name":"Criminal","type":"background","img":"modules/dnd5-all-the-things/media/icons/criminal.png","data":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\">\n<p>You are an experienced criminal with a history of breaking the law. You have spent a lot of time among other criminals and still have contacts within the criminal underworld. You're far closer than most people to the world of murder, theft, and violence that pervades the underbelly of civilization, and you have survived up to this point by flouting the rules and regulations of society.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<hr />\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\">\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Skill Proficiencies:</span></strong> @skill[Deception], @skill[Stealth]</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Tool Proficiencies:</span></strong> One type of <a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/items.html#blankhash,flstsource:phb=1,flstmiscellaneous:mundane=1,flsttype:gaming%20set=1\">gaming set</a>, @item[thieves' tools|phb]</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Equipment:</span> </strong>A @item[crowbar|phb], a set of dark @item[common clothes|phb] including a hood, and a belt @item[pouch|phb] containing 15 gp</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><strong><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Feature: </span></strong><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.ChOvMaSOkQFY5jFr]{Criminal Contact}</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h2 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"24\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Specialty</span></h2>\n<p>There are many kinds of criminals, and within a thieves' guild or similar criminal organization, individual members have particular specialties. Even criminals who operate outside of such organizations have strong preferences for certain kinds of crimes over others. Choose the role you played in your criminal life, or roll on the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.ZaPrSSyFnoPsJwj3]{Criminal: Specialty} table.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h2 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"25\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Suggested Characteristics</span></h2>\n<p>Criminals might seem like villains on the surface, and many of them are villainous to the core. But some have an abundance of endearing, if not redeeming, characteristics. There might be honor among thieves, but criminals rarely show any respect for law or authority.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.ljtn56ptRGUOYgn7]{Criminal: Personality Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.MAkI5H6l7AfBIZaG]{Criminal: Ideal}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.Gle8KTHnlwPoakTt]{Criminal: Bond}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.5d5FLWYf8g3yEXzI]{Criminal: Flaw}</p>\n</div>\n</div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","advancement":[{"_id":"p25u4s8btc99rdc7","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.world.background-features-att.F8JENPyX58JtTCpM","Compendium.world.background-features-att.4y9VTuzBqABgvoVw"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""},{"_id":"20am1wpu22r5zxfd","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.ZySAynuDyrCradrM","Compendium.dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.QDwHMGweZM7FOubw"],"optional":true},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Items","icon":""}],"damage":{"parts":[]},"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":null,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null},"requirements":"","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"agAgpAnkyD85MLSk":3},"flags":{"srd5e":{"page":"backgrounds.html","source":"PHB","hash":"criminal_phb","propDroppable":"background"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MtzY4F9yggD66iU7"}}}
{"_id":"cXD72NVSvniL61Ls","name":"Investigator","type":"background","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>You relentlessly seek the truth. Perhaps you're motivated by belief in the law and a sense of universal justice, or maybe that very law has failed you and you seek to make things right. You could have witnessed something remarkable or terrible, and now you must know more about this hidden truth. Or maybe you're a detective for hire, uncovering secrets for well-paying clients. Whether the mysteries you're embroiled in are local crimes or realm-spanning conspiracies, you're driven by a personal need to hunt down even the most elusive clues and reveal what others would keep hidden in the shadows.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Skill Proficiencies: </strong>Choose two from among Insight, Investigation, or Perception<br /><strong>Tool Proficiencies: </strong>Disguise kit, thieves' tools<br /><strong>Equipment: </strong>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.PBIV523br8r4PJOX]{A magnifying glass}, evidence from a past case (choose one or roll for a trinket from the <a href=\"http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/trinkets\">Horror Trinkets table</a>) a set of @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.ZySAynuDyrCradrM]{Common Clothes}, and 10gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Feature:</strong> @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.uKlwXcvQuz8HCa3w]{Official Inquiry}</p>\n<h1>Path to Mystery</h1>\n<p>Your first case influenced the types of mysteries you're interested in. Why was this case so impactful, personal, or traumatic? Whom did it affect besides you? Why and how did you get involved? Was it solved? How did it set you on the path to investigating other mysteries? Roll on or choose details from the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.Oz9nPuM8EDy5LIDl]{First Case table} to develop the mystery that started your career as an investigator.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Van Richten's Guide to Ravenloft","advancement":[{"_id":"en9fbvu4647c4coj","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.uKlwXcvQuz8HCa3w"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"agAgpAnkyD85MLSk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1FCd1tDklpp4eGSn"}}}
