{"_id":"cXD72NVSvniL61Ls","name":"Investigator","type":"background","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>You relentlessly seek the truth. Perhaps you're motivated by belief in the law and a sense of universal justice, or maybe that very law has failed you and you seek to make things right. You could have witnessed something remarkable or terrible, and now you must know more about this hidden truth. Or maybe you're a detective for hire, uncovering secrets for well-paying clients. Whether the mysteries you're embroiled in are local crimes or realm-spanning conspiracies, you're driven by a personal need to hunt down even the most elusive clues and reveal what others would keep hidden in the shadows.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Skill Proficiencies: </strong>Choose two from among Insight, Investigation, or Perception<br /><strong>Tool Proficiencies: </strong>Disguise kit, thieves' tools<br /><strong>Equipment: </strong>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.PBIV523br8r4PJOX]{A magnifying glass}, evidence from a past case (choose one or roll for a trinket from the <a href=\"http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/trinkets\">Horror Trinkets table</a>) a set of @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.ZySAynuDyrCradrM]{Common Clothes}, and 10gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Feature:</strong> @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.uKlwXcvQuz8HCa3w]{Official Inquiry}</p>\n<h1>Path to Mystery</h1>\n<p>Your first case influenced the types of mysteries you're interested in. Why was this case so impactful, personal, or traumatic? Whom did it affect besides you? Why and how did you get involved? Was it solved? How did it set you on the path to investigating other mysteries? Roll on or choose details from the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.Oz9nPuM8EDy5LIDl]{First Case table} to develop the mystery that started your career as an investigator.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Van Richten's Guide to Ravenloft","advancement":[{"_id":"en9fbvu4647c4coj","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":[],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"agAgpAnkyD85MLSk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1FCd1tDklpp4eGSn"}}}
{"_id":"cXD72NVSvniL61Ls","name":"Investigator","type":"background","img":"https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/core/icons/tools/scribal/magnifying-glass.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>You relentlessly seek the truth. Perhaps you're motivated by belief in the law and a sense of universal justice, or maybe that very law has failed you and you seek to make things right. You could have witnessed something remarkable or terrible, and now you must know more about this hidden truth. Or maybe you're a detective for hire, uncovering secrets for well-paying clients. Whether the mysteries you're embroiled in are local crimes or realm-spanning conspiracies, you're driven by a personal need to hunt down even the most elusive clues and reveal what others would keep hidden in the shadows.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Skill Proficiencies: </strong>Choose two from among Insight, Investigation, or Perception<br /><strong>Tool Proficiencies: </strong>Disguise kit, thieves' tools<br /><strong>Equipment: </strong>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.PBIV523br8r4PJOX]{A magnifying glass}, evidence from a past case (choose one or roll for a trinket from the <a href=\"http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/trinkets\">Horror Trinkets table</a>) a set of @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.items-att.ZySAynuDyrCradrM]{Common Clothes}, and 10gp.</p>\n<p><strong>Feature:</strong> @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.uKlwXcvQuz8HCa3w]{Official Inquiry}</p>\n<h1>Path to Mystery</h1>\n<p>Your first case influenced the types of mysteries you're interested in. Why was this case so impactful, personal, or traumatic? Whom did it affect besides you? Why and how did you get involved? Was it solved? How did it set you on the path to investigating other mysteries? Roll on or choose details from the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.Oz9nPuM8EDy5LIDl]{First Case table} to develop the mystery that started your career as an investigator.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Van Richten's Guide to Ravenloft","advancement":[{"_id":"en9fbvu4647c4coj","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":["Compendium.dnd5-all-the-things.background-features-att.d6CPScFTvvDpVttn"],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"agAgpAnkyD85MLSk":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1FCd1tDklpp4eGSn"}}}
{"_id":"CIpPydJ3S9cClR0B","name":"Sage","type":"background","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-open-brown.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\">\n<p>You spent years learning the lore of the multiverse. You scoured manuscripts, studied scrolls, and listened to the greatest experts on the subjects that interest you. Your efforts have made you a master in your fields of study.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<hr style=\"border-top:1px solid var(--color-border-light-primary);border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border-light-highlight)\" />\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\">\n<ul class=\"rd__list rd__list-hang-notitle\">\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Skill Proficiencies:</span></strong> @skill[Arcana], @skill[History]</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Languages:</span> </strong>Two of your choice</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"rd__li \">\n<p class=\"rd__p-list-item\"><strong><span class=\"bold rd__list-item-name\">Equipment:</span> </strong>A @item[Ink (1-ounce bottle)|phb|bottle of black ink], a quill, a small knife, a letter from a dead colleague posing a question you have not yet been able to answer, a set of @item[common clothes|phb], and a belt @item[pouch|phb] containing 10 gp</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<p><strong>Feature: </strong>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.backgrounds-att.NY0cE3MCTjzw3X3M]{Researcher}</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"2\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Specialty</span></h3>\n<p>To determine the nature of your scholarly training, roll a d8 or choose from the @Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.7nIJ47TPOKsuW6Bl]{Sage: Field of Study}</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\">\n<h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-underline-header)\" data-title-index=\"3\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Suggested Characteristics</span></h3>\n<p>Sages are defined by their extensive studies, and their characteristics reflect this life of study. Devoted to scholarly pursuits, a sage values knowledge highly—sometimes in its own right, sometimes as a means toward other ideals.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.JFPvplBI70B59lTf]{Sage: Personality Trait}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.SGSIGMxVVQpSgHBk]{Sage: Ideal}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.mYLsnHQ99KADwa81]{Sage: Bond}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5-all-the-things.background-tables-att.qcMtCOieagNTeoM2]{Sage: Flaw}</p>\n</div>\n</div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Player's Handbook","advancement":[{"_id":"n4re4c8dtjm5ey6p","type":"ItemGrant","configuration":{"items":[],"optional":false},"value":{},"level":1,"title":"Feature","icon":""}]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EbUDbuCjvuW36J0B":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hbRO096Dv1chMJDL"}}}
